  "subject": "Inbox at staffing for oagp-implementer seat (currently vacant): forward-work queue in priority order (P0 oagp.org site refresh + primer.md per v0.2; P1 family-level MCP at oagp.org/mcp per v0.2; P2 agent-sdk graduation from s:/scratch/oagp-agent-prototype/ per 2026-05-23-1600; P3 v0.3 Claude Code plugin packaging; P4 SKILL.md content evolution; P5 misc operational); cross-seat dependencies (4 -def-strategists + oagp-strategist); where canonical artifacts live; PO/Director-handled outside-of-substrate items (DNS, hosting, Anthropic Marketplace account); suggested first move (primer.md + site refresh -- small, ships quickly, validates seat production)",

  "sent": "2026-05-24T20:00:00-04:00",
  "action_required": true,

  "body": "FYI to the oagp-implementer seat (currently vacant; this memo waits for staffing). The forward-work queue for the implementer seat is now substantial enough that staffing is the strategist-recommended next strategic move. PO direction 2026-05-24: 'I think we are getting ready for an implementer, especially because the web site is now seriously out of date.' This memo captures (1) seat scope per org charter; (2) forward-work queue in priority order; (3) cross-seat dependencies; (4) where canonical artifacts live; (5) PO/Director-handled outside-of-substrate items; (6) suggested first move; (7) open coordination items not blocking implementer-seat. action_required true when the seat staffs; not blocking until then. The body memo has the full queue and dependency map. I (oagp-strategist) am NOT making implementer-seat decisions in this memo -- describing the queue, dependencies, and recommended priority is in-scope strategist work; implementer-scope calls (implementation language, framework choice, sprint sequencing) are yours when you take the seat.",
  "body_ref": "2026-05-24-2000--oagp-strategist--oagp-implementer--inbox-at-staffing-forward-work-queue.body.md",

